column5: Here are some pictures from my cell phone. I was on the gov. dock at the waterfront.           If we don't get a thaw the ice may be drivable for Jan 1st.
I guess,I need to get to plannin' sumphin'   Randy

The satilite images show the lake is froze right across. From my dock all I see is pack ice as far as I can see. We are going to need a good rain to help smooth it out. I will try and get a photo tomorrow. Walked out 100 yards today 5-6".It froze as the wind just kept blowing in more slush.                '

Thank you for the pics Nipfisher. Was talking to a friend that lives on Fish Bay. He said it was open in the center yesterday and the wind was keeping it open. Calmer winds and cold temperatures will certainly take care of that. Glad to see there is little snow on the lake. That will help things get thick in a hurry.
Callander Bay was still wide open on Tuesday when I drove past it. The main lake must have frozen over as of last night.
Sweet, the time is almost upon us LoL....Ice fish baby haha
